  "timeboxMinutes": 35,
  "prompt": "Finance gives you a list of employee ids and asks for each employee's total trip spend.\n\nThere is an async endpoint for one employee at a time. You should fetch several employees concurrently, but not all at once. Then aggregate each employee's trips into a compact result row.\n\nWrite `async def employee_trip_totals(base_url, token, employee_ids, max_concurrency)`.\n\nFake async API:\n\n```python\nimport travel_api\n\ntrips = await travel_api.list_employee_trips(base_url, token, employee_id)\n```\n\n`list_employee_trips` returns a list of trip dicts for that employee. Each trip has `total_cost_cents`.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `list[dict]`.\n- Return one row per input employee id, in the same order as `employee_ids`.\n- Each row should have exactly this shape:\n\n```python\n{\"employee_id\": \"emp_001\", \"total_cents\": 125000, \"trip_count\": 2}\n```\n\n- Include employees with no trips as `{\"employee_id\": employee_id, \"total_cents\": 0, \"trip_count\": 0}`.\n- If an employee id appears more than once in the input, return a row for each occurrence.\n- Respect `max_concurrency`; at most that many employee trip-list calls should be in flight at once.\n- Return `[]` for an empty input list.\n\nDo not fetch the employee list. The caller already decided which employee ids matter. Do not sort by spend; preserve input order.\n\nValidation focus: bounded async fan-out, aggregation, preserving input order, duplicate employee ids, and zero-trip employees.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "employeeTripTotals",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "employee_ids",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "max_concurrency",
        "type": {
          "type": "number"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object"
      }
    }
  },
